cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the design of a convolution neural network accelerator using block floating point arithmetic. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.ET (Embedded Systems), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Among these, cs.AR and cs.CV are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the topic of the paper. cs.NE is also likely as it deals with neural networks, which are the focus of the paper. cs.ET and cs.SY are less likely but still possible as they deal with embedded systems and control, which are relevant to the design of the CNN accelerator.
